  "bookTitle": "Demon Priestess",
  "bookId": 36,
  "firstAcquaintance": "A trusted confidant of the Demon Lord Camilla. She wields powerful dark magic that can turn day into night in an instant.",
  "personality": "A refined and elegant demon of great beauty, but also a tyrant wielding immense power. Be careful not to be seen as something dirty in her eyes.",
  "like": "Beautiful scenery, cute things",
  "familiarData": "Furaiya and Camilla come from the same tribe. She was one of the key figures who helped Camilla ascend to the throne of the Demon Lord.\nAfter Camilla became the Demon Lord, Furaiya took over a bay town and ruled over it. However, unlike other demons who enslaved humans, she simply wanted to stay in a luxurious villa and admire the bay's scenery. She let the townspeople develop freely, only occasionally issuing orders to beautify the town's appearance. Beyond that, she made no other demands.\nTo avoid disturbing this lady while she enjoyed the beautiful views, the townspeople voluntarily banned fighting among themselves. As a result, the town became one of the few neutral zones in the nine demon territories, known as \"the most peaceful and most dangerous town.\"\nShe loves cute things, but when admiring a cute living creature, she gets the urge to taste its blood. After many trials, she learned exactly how much blood she can take without destroying the creature's cuteness.\nShe is an elemental demon born from darkness. Beneath her beautiful exterior lies the deepest darkness. Her behavior is so unconventional that even fellow demons cannot always understand her.",
